        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 6:52AM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 652 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Findley Lake to Andover. Movement was
southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Meadville, Corry, Titusville, Union City, Cambridge Springs,
Linesville, Wattsburg, Adamsville, Canadohta Lake, Pymatuning
Central, Riceville, Harmonsburg, Lincolnville, Guys Mills, Pymatuning
North, Atlantic, Cochranton, Saegertown, Conneaut Lake, and
Jamestown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
